'''Mid-Western Regional Maternity Hospital''' is a hospital in [[County Limerick]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].

It is listed in the proposals of the ''[[Protection of Life During Pregnancy Act 2013|Protection of Life During Pregnancy Bill 2013]]'' as one of the institutions where [[abortion]]s could be carried out in the event of the passage of the Bill.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/list-of-institutions-where-limited-abortions-can-be-carried-out-1.1427300|title=List of institutions where limited abortions can be carried out|publisher=Irish Times|date=June 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oireachtas.ie/documents/bills28/bills/2013/6613/b6613d.pdf|title=Protection of Life During Pregnancy Bill 2013|publisher=Houses of the Oireachtas|accessdate=18 July 2013}}</ref>

According to the ''[[Limerick Leader]]'' newspaper, the hospital is expected later in 2013 to become part of the [[University of Limerick Hospitals Group]], within which it will be re-branded with a new name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.limerickleader.ie/news/leader-local/regional-hospital-name-consigned-to-history-1-5218960|title=Regional Hospital name consigned to history|date=June 25, 2013|publisher=Limerick Leader|author=Mike Dwane}}</ref>

